	"keywords": "javascript",
	"description": "In JavaScript, hoisting allows you to use functions and variables before they&#x27;re\ndeclared. In this post, we&#x27;ll learn what hoisting is and how it works.\n\nWhat is hoisting?\nTake a look at the code below and guess what happens when it runs:\n\nconsole.log(foo);\nvar foo &#x3D; &#x27;foo&#x27;;\n\n\nIt might surprise you that this code outputs undefined and doesn&#x27;t fail or throw\nan error – even though foo gets assigned after we console.log it!\n\nThis is because the JavaScript interpreter splits the declaration and assign",
	"headline": "What is Hoisting in JavaScript?",
